    "created_at": "2017-01-05T17:31:05Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-01-05T17:31:05Z",
    "body": "I tracked down and it turns out [this `return`](https://github.com/electron/electron/blob/df179ed28d6e84cae8de3e24594f44e59924cd52/atom/browser/native_window.cc#L580) causes the issue, but I think this is necessary, because if it doesn't return when the background is set, the background color wouldn't be preserved and it will be transparent. So I think the expected behavior in the current state is the white background, because you didn't specify the window transparency.\r\n\r\nThough we could force the window to be transparent by default, when vibrancy is set. Thoughts?"
  },
