    "created_at": "2017-01-06T03:20:05Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-01-06T03:20:05Z",
    "body": "> I tracked down and it turns out this return causes the issue, but I think this is necessary, because if it doesn't return when the background is set, the background color wouldn't be preserved and it will be transparent. So I think the expected behavior in the current state is the white background, because you didn't specify the window transparency.\r\n\r\nThanks for tracking it down @gerhardberger. I can confirm that setting the `BrowserWindow` `transparent` option fixes the current behavior.\r\n\r\n> Though we could force the window to be transparent by default, when vibrancy is set. Thoughts?\r\n\r\nI couldn't seem to see a documented `setTransparent` method on the `BrowserWindow`, does this mean it's currently not possible to change that property after the window has been created?\r\n\r\nIf it is possible (but there's just no current API for it), I think it would make sense to set the window to transparent if there's a vibrancy set."
  },
